=== 事件定性：网络战争行为还是网络间谍行为？ ===
这次攻击引发了一场辩论：这次黑客攻击应该被视为网络间谍活动还是[[網絡戰|网络战争]]行为？<ref name="reuters-2020-12-19-espionage">{{Cite web|title=Explainer-U.S. government hack: espionage or act of war?|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/global-cyber-legal/explainer-us-government-hack-espionage-or-act-of-war-idUKL1N2IY3EH|accessdate=2020-12-19|author=Wolfe|date=2020-12-19|first=Jan|work=Reuters}}</ref> 

大多数现任和前任美国官员认为，2020年的此次黑客攻击是“令人震惊的间谍行为”，但由于攻击者没有破坏或篡改行为，也没有造成对基础设施（如对电网、电信网络等）的实际损害，所以不是网络战争。<ref name="nbc-2020-12-18-espionage">{{Cite web|title=Suspected Russian hack: Was it an epic cyber attack or spy operation?|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/suspected-russian-hack-was-it-epic-cyber-attack-or-spy-n1251766|accessdate=2020-12-19|author=Dilanian|date=2020-12-18|first=Ken|work=NBC News|archive-date=2021-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210311005453/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/suspected-russian-hack-was-it-epic-cyber-attack-or-spy-n1251766|dead-url=no}}</ref>大西洋理事会、哥伦比亚萨尔茨曼研究所的埃里卡·博格哈德和胡佛协会、海军战争学院的杰奎琳·施耐德认为，这次入侵是一种间谍行为，可以用“逮捕、外交或反间谍”来回应，而且尚未被证明是一次在法律上允许美国以武力回应的网络战争行为。<ref name="wired-2020-12-17">{{Cite magazine|last=Erica Borghard|last2=Jacquelyn Schneider|title=Russia's Hack Wasn't Cyberwar. That Complicates US Strategy|url=https://www.wired.com/story/russia-solarwinds-hack-wasnt-cyberwar-us-strategy/|magazine=Wired|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218062246/https://www.wired.com/story/russia-solarwinds-hack-wasnt-cyberwar-us-strategy/|archive-date=December 18, 2020|access-date=December 17, 2020}}</ref>法学教授杰克·戈德史密斯写道，这次黑客攻击是一次具有破坏性的网络间谍行为，但“并不违反国际法或国际规范”，并写道，“由于美国自身的做法，美国政府历来承认外国政府在美国政府网络中从事网络间谍活动的合法性。”<ref name="dispatch-2020-12-18">{{Cite web|title=Self-Delusion on the Russia Hack|url=https://thedispatch.com/p/self-delusion-on-the-russia-hack|author=Goldsmith|first=Jack|work=thedispatch.com|access-date=2021-03-03|archive-date=2021-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516174301/https://thedispatch.com/p/self-delusion-on-the-russia-hack|dead-url=no}}</ref> 法学教授迈克尔·施密特对此引用了《塔林手册》的例子以表示赞同。<ref name="js-2020-12-21">{{Cite web|title=Russia's SolarWinds Operation and International Law|url=https://www.justsecurity.org/73946/russias-solarwinds-operation-and-international-law/|date=December 21, 2020|work=Just Security|access-date=2021-03-03|archive-date=2021-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210529171905/https://www.justsecurity.org/73946/russias-solarwinds-operation-and-international-law/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

相比之下，微软总裁布拉德·史密斯将此次黑客攻击称为网络战争，称“即使是在数字时代，这也不是‘像往常一样的间谍活动’。因为它‘不仅针对特定目标，而且是对全球关键网络基础设施可靠性的攻击’”<ref name="nbc-2020-12-18-espionage"/><ref name="at-2020-12-18">{{Cite web|title=Microsoft president calls SolarWinds hack an 'act of recklessness'|url=https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2020/12/only-an-elite-few-solarwinds-hack-victims-received-follow-on-attacks/|accessdate=December 18, 2020|date=December 18, 2020|work=Ars Technica|archive-date=2021-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210507202218/https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2020/12/only-an-elite-few-solarwinds-hack-victims-received-follow-on-attacks/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="bbc-2020-12-18">{{Cite web|title=US cyber-attack: US energy department confirms it was hit by Sunburst hack|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-55358332|accessdate=December 18, 2020|date=December 18, 2020|work=BBC News|archive-date=2021-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210606191413/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-55358332|dead-url=no}}</ref>美国参议员理查德·杜宾称此次袭击相当于一场宣战。<ref name="dn-2020-12-17"/><ref name="nyt-2020-12-16">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/16/us/politics/russia-hack-putin-trump-biden.html|title=Billions Spent on U.S. Defenses Failed to Detect Giant Russian Hack|first=David E.|author=Sanger|first2=Nicole|author2=Perlroth|first3=Julian E.|last3=Barnes|date=December 16, 2020|work=The New York Times|accessdate=December 16, 2020|archivedate=December 16, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201216200710/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/16/us/politics/russia-hack-putin-trump-biden.html}}</ref>

=== 关于美国可能的报复行为的辩论 ===
为《连线》杂志撰稿的博格哈德和施耐德认为，美国“应该继续建立并依靠战略威慑来说服各国不要将其收集的网络情报武器化”。他们还表示，由于威慑可能无法有效阻止威胁行为者的网络间谍企图，美国还应该通过加强网络防御、更好的信息共享和“前沿防御”（减少俄罗斯和中国的攻击性网络能力）等方法，降低网络间谍活动的成功率。<ref name="wired-2020-12-17">{{Cite magazine|last=Erica Borghard|last2=Jacquelyn Schneider|title=Russia's Hack Wasn't Cyberwar. That Complicates US Strategy|url=https://www.wired.com/story/russia-solarwinds-hack-wasnt-cyberwar-us-strategy/|magazine=Wired|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218062246/https://www.wired.com/story/russia-solarwinds-hack-wasnt-cyberwar-us-strategy/|archive-date=December 18, 2020|access-date=December 17, 2020}}</ref>

戈德史密斯在为《''The Dispatch''》撰写的文章中写道：防御和威慑网络入侵战略的失败，应该促使美国考虑采取“相互克制”战略。“即美国减少在外国网络中的某些（间谍）活动，来换取对手在美国网络中的宽容。”<ref name="dispatch-2020-12-18"/>

网络安全作家[[布魯斯·施奈爾|布鲁斯·施奈尔]]反对报复或增强攻击能力，他建议采取一种以防御为主导的战略，并建议签署《网络空间信任与安全巴黎倡议》或参与全球网络空间稳定委员会（Global Commission on the Stability of Cyberspace）。<ref name="gu-2020-12-23-schneier">{{Cite web|title=The US has suffered a massive cyberbreach. It's hard to overstate how bad it is | Bruce Schneier|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/dec/23/cyber-attack-us-security-protocols|author=Schneier|date=December 23, 2020|first=Bruce|access-date=2021-03-03|archive-date=2021-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210507091101/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/dec/23/cyber-attack-us-security-protocols|dead-url=no}}</ref>

为《纽约时报》撰文时，前中央情报局特工、哈佛大学贝尔弗科学与国际事务中心情报项目主任保罗·科尔贝（Paul Kolbe）赞同了施奈尔的呼吁，要求美国改进网络防御和国际协议。他还指出，美国也在参与针对其它国家的类似行动，他称这是一场相互的网络冲突。<ref name="nyt-2020-12-23">{{Cite web|title=Opinion | With Hacking, the United States Needs to Stop Playing the Victim|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/23/opinion/russia-united-states-hack.html|author=Kolbe|date=December 24, 2020|first=Paul R.|access-date=2021-03-03|archive-date=2021-05-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519021103/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/23/opinion/russia-united-states-hack.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在《Slate》杂志上，弗雷德·卡普兰发表评论称，自1967年以来，导致这种计算机网络入侵的结构性问题已经为公众所知，而且历届美国政府都未能实施相关专家反复要求的结构性防御措施。<ref name="slate-2020-12-18">{{Cite web|title=The Government Has Known About the Vulnerabilities That Allowed Russia's Latest Hack for Decades—and Chose Not to Fix Them|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/12/solarwinds-russian-hack-cybersecurity.html|author=Kaplan|date=December 18, 2020|first=Fred|work=Slate Magazine|access-date=2021-03-03|archive-date=2021-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516194855/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/12/solarwinds-russian-hack-cybersecurity.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>他指出，对间谍活动的过激反应与美国利益相左，而加强防御并明确应对网络冲突政策将是更有成效的策略。<ref name="slate-2020-12-23">{{Cite web|title=Should the U.S. Retaliate for Russia's Big Hack?|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/12/solarwinds-hack-retaliation-options-cyberwar-russia.html|author=Kaplan|date=December 23, 2020|first=Fred|work=Slate Magazine|access-date=2021-03-03|archive-date=2021-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506045057/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/12/solarwinds-hack-retaliation-options-cyberwar-russia.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

